title: 820-3209  pch getting hot and error code  4sns/1/c0000008
message:
customers 3209 had liquid damage. 3v3 on the jtag was corroded pulled it and put new solder. board came to life and is working but running a bit sluggish,  dio gave me error code  4sns/1/c0000008. phc is getting really hot but cpu is fine.  any ideas? 

Tried replacing u5510 sensor but no change.

title: 820-3209  pch getting hot and error code  4sns/1/c0000008
message: Do I really still need to tell you to run a REAL ASD instead of built in garbage?
